page.title: 11TRANSPORT.
page.content: The main road in our grid is the A40 which runs north of the grid.During the year of 1985 we did a survey on transport.Over 60% of Eynshams population have got a car and most people have got a bicycles,but some people havn't got a bicycles and cars.We have different makes of cars like:Ford and Austin.The main source of power used in our cars is Petrol. Two buses run in Eynsham.One goes to Church Hanborough which is about 2.5 miles away.One bus goes 17 times in a week and one only comes twice.We have motorcars that can go up too 170 mph but we are only can go 70 mph as a max.speed. BY ROGER MARSHALL,MARK SKIDMORE AND MATTHEW TREADWELL.
